[31m-# Fluid Layouts and Typography[m
[31m-[m
[31m-## Overview[m
[31m-[m
[31m-Fluid design creates smooth scaling experiences by using relative units and mathematical functions instead of fixed breakpoints. This approach reduces the need for media queries and creates more natural-feeling interfaces.[m
[31m-[m
[31m-## Fluid Typography[m
[31m-[m
[31m-### The clamp() Function[m
[31m-[m
[31m-```css[m
[31m-/* clamp(minimum, preferred, maximum) */[m
[31m-.heading {[m
[31m-  /* Never smaller than 1.5rem, never larger than 3rem */[m
[31m-  /* Scales at 5vw between those values */[m
[31m-  font-size: clamp(1.5rem, 5vw, 3rem);[m
[31m-}[m
[31m-```[m
[31m-[m
[31m-### Calculating Fluid Values[m
[31m-[m
[31m-The preferred value in `clamp()` typically combines a base size with a viewport-relative portion:[m
[31m-[m
[31m-```css[m
[31m-/* Formula: clamp(min, base + scale * vw, max) */[m
[31m-[m
[31m-/* For text that scales from 16px (320px viewport) to 24px (1200px viewport): */[m
[31m-/* slope = (24 - 16) / (1200 - 320) = 8 / 880 = 0.00909 */[m
[31m-/* y-intercept = 16 - 0.00909 * 320 = 13.09px = 0.818rem */[m
[31m-[m
[31m-.text {[m
[31m-  font-size: clamp(1rem, 0.818rem + 0.909vw, 1.5rem);[m
[31m-}[m
[31m-```[m
[31m-[m
[31m-### Type Scale Generator[m
[31m-[m
[31m-```javascript[m
[31m-// Generate a fluid type scale[m
[31m-function fluidType({[m
[31m-  minFontSize,[m
[31m-  maxFontSize,[m
[31m-  minViewport = 320,[m
[31m-  maxViewport = 1200,[m
[31m-}) {[m
[31m-  const minFontRem = minFontSize / 16;[m
[31m-  const maxFontRem = maxFontSize / 16;[m
[31m-  const minViewportRem = minViewport / 16;[m
[31m-  const maxViewportRem = maxViewport / 16;[m
[31m-[m
[31m-  const slope = (maxFontRem - minFontRem) / (maxViewportRem - minViewportRem);[m
[31m-  const yAxisIntersection = minFontRem - slope * minViewportRem;[m
[31m-[m
[31m-  return `clamp(${minFontRem}rem, ${yAxisIntersection.toFixed(4)}rem + ${(slope * 100).toFixed(4)}vw, ${maxFontRem}rem)`;[m
[31m-}[m
[31m-[m
[31m-// Usage[m
[31m-const typeScale = {[m
[31m-  xs: fluidType({ minFontSize: 12, maxFontSize: 14 }),[m
